{
  "stem": "9730.1",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 3.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, I had four years of elementary school in Walldorf, after which I switched to a-- a high school, actually, a level above normal high school, in Heidelberg, where I also had four years.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "At that point, it was 1934, and the decrees against the Jews, and especially the economic decrees, had gotten to a point where my father found it extremely difficult to pay the tuition that it took for-- for high school in Germany.",
      "word_count": 42
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And so it was thought best that I take up a trade or do something that Jewish young people were still allowed to do, because by that time, we-- we felt some of the restrictions that were being imposed.",
      "word_count": 39
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And so I-- I always having liked books and literature and so on, thought that the closest thing to that might be to go into the printing business, which I did.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, both-- both my sister and my brother were considerably older than I, by-- my sister by 9 years, and my-- my brother by 12.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And so they actually left home, you know, while I was still growing up in my home.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And, of course, I-- my sister was there a little longer.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But my brother left home fairly early-- I almost don't remember him living under the same roof-- and went to-- to larger cities, such as, well, first, Mannheim, Stuttgart, and-- and Breslau, where he-- he was really a railroad buff, all-- even as a very young boy.",
      "word_count": 47
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And so it was quite clear for him that he would go into the travel business.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And he went with one of the large steamship companies in-- in Breslau, which allowed him also to maintain-- he-- he could recite railroad schedules by heart.",
      "word_count": 27
    }
  ],
